<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06021107 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06021107 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  OBITUARY; CAMPBELL; WOMAN  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Minnie L. Berg, foster mother to more than 100 children, died Sunday atDriftwood Convalescent Hospital in Campbell.;    She was 79. She wasrecovering from a bout with cancer, but the cause of death was not immediatelyknown.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  MINNIE BERG, LONGTIME FOSTER MOTHER  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Obituaries  </MEMO><TEXT>     According to her son, Vic, Mrs. Berg began hosting foster children duringWorld War II at her Daly City home.;    After she moved to Campbell in 1944with her late husband, Guy, she became active in Santa Clara County's fostercare program.;    &quot;I had brothers all the time -- sometimes six at a time,&quot;said Vic, an only child. &quot;Some stayed 10 years with us.&quot;;    Vic Berg said hismother hosted more than 100 foster children between 1944 and 1964, a few ofwhom had kept in contact with Mrs. Berg.;    &quot;I think she began during the warwhen there was a real need for foster families. I guess it's obvious, but sheloved children,&quot; he said.;    Santa Clara County had honored Mrs. Berg for herlong service as a foster parent.;    Mrs. Berg was born in Half Moon Bay in1911 and moved to Daly City in 1941. Her husband, who served in the Navy 30years, died in 1976.;    In addition to her son, Vic, of Stockton, Mrs. Bergis survived by two grandchildren, Chris Berg of Lodi and Susan Bennett ofWoodbridge; and two great-grandchildren, Daniel and Ethan Bennett ofWoodbridge.;    A funeral service will be held at 11 a.m. Wednesday atDarling-Fischer Campbell Memorial Chapel. Burial will be in Los Gatos MemorialPark, San Jose.  </TEXT><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  SAN JOSE MERCURY NEWS  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910121  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Monday  </DAY><MONTH>  January  </MONTH><PG.COL>  3B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  258  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Monday January 21, 199100021107,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>